article.description: — Noah Fernandes had a career-high 29 points as 10-seed UMass beat seven-seed George Washington 99-88 in the second round of the Atlantic 10 Conference tournament on Thursday night.
article.headline: Fernandes lifts UMass past George Washington 99-88 in A10
article.linkText: Fernandes lifts UMass past George Washington 99-88 in A10
article.story: WASHINGTON -- — Noah Fernandes had a career-high 29 points as 10-seed UMass beat seven-seed George Washington 99-88 in the second round of the Atlantic 10 Conference tournament on Thursday night. T.J. Weeks Jr. had 15 points for UMass (15-16). C.J. Kelly also scored 15 points. Trent Buttrick had 13 points and 16 rebounds. Joe Bamisile had 25 points for the Colonials (12-18). Brayon Freeman added 18 points and seven assists. James Bishop had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
